{"timestamp": "2025-12-04 18:22:56.117940", "event": "llm_start", "messages": "content='Based on the diagnosis report: Troubleshooting Diagnosis Report\\n\\nSummary\\n- Detected anomaly: Network 10.0.1.0/24 (host pc_0_1) is unreachable from the rest of the fabric. All pings to 10.0.1.2 return “Destination Net Unreachable” from the local gateway of the source host.\\n- Localization: The issue is isolated to leaf_router_0_1’s EBGP adjacency to both spines. All other EBGP sessions in the fabric appear healthy.\\n- Root cause: Misconfigured BGP local AS on leaf_router_0_1 (set to 65801 instead of the expected 65201), causing EBGP sessions with the spines to fail, and preventing advertisement of 10.0.1.0/24 to the fabric.\\n\\nObserved Symptoms and Impact\\n- End-to-end reachability:\\n  - pc_0_0 → pc_0_1 (10.0.1.2) fails with “From 10.0.0.1 Destination Net Unreachable.”\\n  - Multiple other hosts attempting to reach 10.0.1.2 fail with “Destination Net Unreachable” from their local default gateway, indicating missing route distribution fabric-wide.\\n  - Other destinations (e.g., 10.1.0.2) are reachable from many hosts, suggesting the rest of the fabric is healthy.\\n- Local connectivity:\\n  - pc_0_1 can reach its directly connected leaf (leaf_router_0_1 at 172.16.0.35), confirming intact host-to-leaf link and IP configuration.\\n\\nControl Plane Findings (FRR/BGP)\\n- leaf_router_0_1:\\n  - BGP summary shows 4 peers (spines) all stuck in Idle and never established.\\n  - Running config: router bgp 65801 with neighbors to spines. Network 10.0.1.0/24 is configured for advertisement.\\n  - FRR log shows repeated connection/reset messages consistent with EBGP session failure.\\n- Spines:\\n  - spine_router_0_0 and spine_router_0_1 BGP summaries:\\n    - Neighbors to leaf_router_0_1 appear as remote-as 65201 and are in Active (not established).\\n    - Other neighbors (including leaf_router_0_0 in AS 65200 and other leaves) are Established with routes exchanged.\\n  - show ip route 10.0.1.0/24 on both spines: “% Network not in table” (route absent).\\n- leaf_router_0_0:\\n  - BGP in AS 65200, fully established with both spines, receiving/sending prefixes as expected.\\n\\nData Plane/Interface State\\n- leaf_router_0_1 interfaces:\\n  - All interconnects to spines and the host-facing interface are up with correct /31 and /24 addressing:\\n    - eth0 172.16.0.35/31 (peer .34), eth1 172.16.0.43/31 (peer .42), eth2 172.16.0.51/31 (peer .50), eth3 172.16.0.59/31 (peer .58), and host-facing eth4 10.0.1.1/24.\\n  - Kernel routing table only shows connected routes; no learned routes from BGP (consistent with BGP down).\\n\\nRoot Cause\\n- BGP AS mismatch on leaf_router_0_1:\\n  - leaf_router_0_1 is configured as local AS 65801.\\n  - Spines are configured to peer with leaf_router_0_1 using remote-as 65201.\\n  - This mismatch prevents EBGP session establishment, so 10.0.1.0/24 is not propagated. Consequently, the rest of the fabric lacks a route to 10.0.1.0/24, causing “Destination Net Unreachable” from source gateways.\\n\\nDevices Implicated\\n- Primary faulty device: leaf_router_0_1 (misconfigured BGP local AS).\\n- Collateral effect: Both spines (spine_router_0_0 and spine_router_0_1) lack a route to 10.0.1.0/24 due to the upstream misconfiguration on the leaf.\\n\\nEvidence Highlights\\n- Ping failures to 10.0.1.2 from multiple hosts with “Destination Net Unreachable” sourced from local leaf gateways.\\n- leaf_router_0_1: show ip bgp summary → all peers Idle; running-config shows router bgp 65801.\\n- Spines: show ip bgp summary → neighbors 172.16.0.35/0.43 (leaf 0_1) remote-as 65201 in Active; show ip route 10.0.1.0/24 → not in table.\\n- leaf_router_0_0: EBGP sessions Established in AS 65200 (normal), indicating problem is isolated to leaf_router_0_1.\\n\\nNo remediation actions are provided at this stage, per request., please provide the submission. Do not submit if no report available.' additional_kwargs={} response_metadata={} id='c6237c11-d060-4f71-97bd-f343c99f8e3b'", "model": {"lc": 1, "type": "constructor", "id": ["langchain", "chat_models", "openai", "ChatOpenAI"], "kwargs": {"model_name": "gpt-5", "openai_api_key": {"lc": 1, "type": "secret", "id": ["OPENAI_API_KEY"]}, "stream_usage": true}, "name": "ChatOpenAI"}}
